com.serena.dmclient.objects
Interface BaselineTemplate

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsObject
public interface BaselineTemplate
extends DimensionsObject

Represents a Dimensions Baseline Template.

A baseline template is defined as a set of rules or criteria whose purpose is to limit the items or requests to be selected for inclusion within a baseline. In Dimensions, baselines are created subject to the rules specified in a Baseline Template.

A rule is defined against an item or request type, and specifies the conditions the lifecycle status of the item or request must satisfy in order for it to be included in the baseline.

Note: Baseline templates are defined at a global (base database) level and are not associated with a specific product. A Dimensions product is only used to restrict the list of item and request types when defining a new template or editing the details of an existing one.

getScope

TypeScope getScope()
                   throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Returns the scope of the baseline template.

Note that you do not set the scope of a baseline template when creating it, and it is not possible to change the scope of an existing baseline template. The scope is fixed at creation time, depending which of the two BaselineTemplates collections (either item or request baseline templates) that the BaselineTemplates.add(BaselineTemplateDetails) method is called on.

Returns:
type scope object
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs
See Also:
TypeScope, Product.getItemBaselineTemplates(), Product.getRequestBaselineTemplates()
